    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe prompt buffer tries to guess where the `':` mark should be but if a plugin edits the buffer, then the mark may be wrong and the user can edit stuff that was intended to be readonly.\n\n`nvim_buf_set_mark(0, ':', 1, ,1, {})` fails, as does `m:`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nPlugins can set the `':` mark.\n\n- `nvim_buf_set_mark(0, ':', 1, ,1, {})`\n- Maybe `m:` should also work.\n\ncc @shadmansaleh ",
    "closed_at": "2025-09-08T22:09:50Z",
